Key Match Events: Anthony Davis dominated the game, scoring 36 points and grabbing 16 rebounds, while getting to the line 15 times.
Bronny James checked into the game with LeBron, becoming the first father-son duo to play in an NBA game together.
Post-Match Reflections: The Wolves struggled to get stops when Rudy Gobert sat down, which will be something that needs to be figured out over the course of the season.
The team's clunky offense and lack of energy were issues that need to be worked out.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Lakers won 110-103, with Anthony Davis outscoring Anthony Edwards 36-27.
The Wolves will stay on the West Coast in California to face the Sacramento Kings on Thursday, 10/24 at 9:00pm CT.
Others: Rudy Gobert being a force on the glass and active offensively
Three-point volume being up, though they have to hit at a higher clip
Nickeil Alexander-Walker hitting his threes and being a team-high +13
